Snap Finance LLC seeks two full-time Analytics Data Scientists in Salt Lake City, UT. Responsibilities include model development and deployment and compiling/analyzing data from multiple sources with the objective of reducing finance underwriting risk, empowering consumers and broadening our influence in a rapidly growing market of alternative finance.
Responsibilities:
Mining, modeling, analyzing large datasets, and utilizing predictive modeling techniques with an emphasis on optimizing credit risk and analyzing customer behavior;
Building and validating a variety of statistical models, providing analytic support, and developing new criteria or strategies;
Compiling appropriate data, applying multidimensional data aggregation and performing profile analysis to evaluate business impact;
Conducting required portfolio analyses incorporating project design, data collection, and analysis, summarizing findings and presenting results in a way non-technical people can understand;
Handling a large volume of transaction-level data utilizing interpretive and problem-solving skills to process and efficiently derive actionable results;
Interacting with stakeholders to understand their business questions, crafting methodologies to mine or analyze datasets and ultimately deliver insightful recommendations to stakeholders;
Minimum Requirements:
Master’s degree in Statistics, Engineering, Econometrics, Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science, Quantitative Social Science, Quantitative Finance or related.
6 months of experience as a Data Scientist or related. Experience, in aggregate, must include:
One or more modeling/machine learning programming environments such as R or Python o Mining data (network mining, social media mining, database mining, etc.)
 Software engineering best practices and architecture (High-performance computing (HPC), relational databases, version control, etc.)
Classification methods (e.g., Neural Net, Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, KNN, Random Forest) o Regression methods (e.g., Linear, Nonlinear, Boosted Regression Trees)
Completion of several projects that demonstrate a strong foundation in data science, data analytics, or visual analytics (e.g., Hypothesis testing, experimental design, network analytics
Strong SQL and database management skills
Application will be accepted via our website or mail resume and cover letter to Snap Finance, Attn: Talent Acquisition, Analytic Data Scientist, 1193 W 2400 S, Salt Lake City, UT 84119.

